#Text=Aragua
#Text=Aragua is a state in north central Venezuela .
#Text=It is famous for its fertile valleys and beautiful beaches , and is within easy reach of Caracas
#Text=Cities
#Text=( Capital )
#Text=- a fascinating town hidden in the mountains outside Caracas , still populated by descendents of a colony of German settlers who built the town from scratch in the 19th century .
#Text=Today , the town is a popular weekend escape for Caraqueños who enjoy its cool climate , restaurants serving traditional German food and locally brewed beer .
#Text=Locally grown produce such as strawberries and raspberries are also sold .
#Text=-
#Text=probably Venezuela 's most popular beach destination for foreign travellers with a great after dark atmosphere , plenty of restaurants and posadas .

#Text=Cata - together with neighbouring Catica , this is another good Aragua beach resort in a beautiful bay , albeit somewhat spoiled by the construction of two tall apartment buildings just behind the beach .
#Text=Other destinations
#Text=Henri Pittier National Park - Venezuela 's first national park , covering the mountains that separate Maracay from the coast .
#Text=Cloudforest and plenty of wildlife .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Buses from the Caracas La Bandera bus terminal go to Maracay ( 1.5 hours ) and La Victoria ( 1 hour ) .
#Text=Change at Maracay for buses to Choroni ( 2 hours ) .
#Text=Get around
#Text=A railway linking Aragua with Caracas is under construction but all travel at present is by road .
#Text=A fast highway runs the length of the state .
#Text=See
#Text=Santa Teresa Rum (
#Text=It is located in the village of El Consejo , close to La Victoria ) .
#Text=This excellent family owned rum plantation is open to the public at weekends , with tours and a tasting session .
#Text=It is the home of arguably Venezuela 's best rum , the " 1796 " brand , which is carefully aged in oak barrels .

#Text=Rancho Grande Biological Station ( From Maracay , take the road to Ocumare-Limon and the station is about 45 minutes outside the city , on the right hand side just after the Rancho Grande Restaurant ( which only usually opens at weekends ) .
#Text=Buses to Ocumare leave from Maracay 's bus terminal , and ask the driver to drop you off at Rancho Grande .
#Text=This ecological research post is run by Venezuela 's prestigious Central University , hidden in the Henri Pittier National Park .
#Text=Do
#Text=Hang gliding is offered close to La Colonia Tovar , on the road down towards La Victoria .
#Text=Eat

#Text=The Hacienda Santa Teresa 's Zafra restaurant , in El Consejo , is open weekends until sundown , offering interesting variations of traditional Venezuelan dishes with a rum theme , as well as international dishes .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=Hotel El Recreo , ☏ +582443210244 .
#Text=Av Intercomunal , La Victoria .
#Text=A converted colonial era farm , this pleasant hotel is a lovely retreat with a good terrace restaurant and swimming pool .
#Text=Certainly the best option in La Victoria .
